Sentencas: A highly efficient Ruddlesden-Popper structure anode material with a formula of Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-delta (RP-SFMN) has been developed for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells (HF-SOFC) application.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is demonstrated that a nanostructured RP-SFMN anode decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles (Ni@RP-SFMN) has been successfully prepared by annealing the anode in reducing atmosphere similar to the operating conditions.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase compositions, valence states, morphologies, and electrocatalytic activities of RP-SFMN material have been characterized in detail.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the in-situ exsolution mechanism of the metallic Ni phase from the parent oxide is clearly explained by using density function theory calculation.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The peak output power density at 800 degrees C is significantly enhanced from 0.163 to 0.409 W/cm(2) while the electrode polarization resistance is effectively lowered from 0.96 to 0.30 Omega cm(2) by the substitution of B-site Fe by Ni, which is attributed to the improved electrocatalytic activities induced by the in-situ exsolved Ni nanocatalysts.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the single cell with RP-SFMN anode exhibits good stability in 3% H2O humidified H-2 and syngas for 110 and 60 h at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our findings indicate that RP-SFMN is a greatly promising anode candidate of HF-SOFCs due to its good electrochemical performance and stability during the operation.
Titulo: Robust Ruddlesden-Popper phase Sr3Fe1.3Mo0.5Ni0.2O7-δ decorated with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells
